        <description>The AMMOS-PDS Pipeline Service (APPS) PDS Label Assistant for Interactive Design (PLAID) online tool allows users to build a PDS4 template using a GUI-based wizard interface that ensures a PDS4 compliant label is built by providing PDS4 documentation and rules inline with the tool. Each step is dynamically generated from the PDS4 schema chosen when the user starts building a PDS4 label. PDS4 xml is built after each step and the user can export their label when they have completed the wizard.</description>
